[[Category:pages to sort]][[cdo:9 nguŏk 16 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:9 goe̍h 16 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[Category:pages to sort]][[zh-yue:九月十六]] {{Lunisolar September}} '''September 16''' is the 16th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Emperor Sujin|ja|崇神天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|86 BC|ja|紀元前86|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 12|ja|10月12日|12=draft|12=draft}}） – The imperial court conducted its first nationwide population and household registration. * {{ill|Shōryaku|ja|正暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|991|ja|991|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 26|ja|10月26日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Emperor Ichijō|ja|一条天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} conferred the title of {{ill|Nyoin-gō|ja|女院号|12=draft|12=draft}} upon the empress dowager, {{ill|Saneko Fujiwara|ja|藤原詮子|12=draft|12=draft}}, marking the first instance of a 【female院号】. * {{ill|Ōtoku|ja|応徳|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1086|ja|1086|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 26|ja|10月26日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Fujiwara Michitoshi|ja|藤原通俊|12=draft|12=draft}} compiled the anthology {{ill|Goshūi Wakashū|ja|後拾遺和歌集|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Births == * {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永|12=draft|12=draft}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1779|ja|1779|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 25|ja|10月25日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ichikawa Beian|ja|市河米庵|12=draft|12=draft}}, a calligrapher ({{ill|Calligrapher|ja|書家|12=draft|12=draft}}) (died {{ill|1858|ja|1858|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Kansei|ja|寛政|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1793|ja|1793|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 20|ja|10月20日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Watanabe Kasan|ja|渡辺崋山|12=draft|12=draft}}, a rangaku scholar and painter (died {{ill|1841|ja|1841|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Bunka|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1804|ja|1804|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 19|ja|10月19日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hosokawa Saigo|ja|細川斉護|12=draft|12=draft}}, the head of the {{ill|Kumamoto Domain|ja|熊本藩|12=draft|12=draft}} (died {{ill|1860|ja|1860|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1855|ja|1855|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 26|ja|10月26日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Komura Jutaro|ja|小村壽太郎|12=draft|12=draft}}, Minister of Foreign Affairs (died {{ill|1911|ja|1911|12=draft|12=draft}}).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tennen|ja|天永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1111|ja|1111|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ōe Masafusa|ja|大江匡房|12=draft|12=draft}}, a kugyō, Confucian scholar, and poet (born {{ill|1041|ja|1041|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Genkyū|ja|元久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1204|ja|1204|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 27|ja|11月27日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hojo Masanori|ja|北条政範|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander (武将) (born {{ill|1189|ja|1189|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1839|ja|1839|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 10|ja|12月10日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Matsudaira Saiatsu|ja|松平斉厚|12=draft|12=draft}}, a daimyō (born {{ill|1783|ja|1783|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1856|ja|1856|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 2|ja|12月2日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ashidai Hirokun|ja|足代弘訓|12=draft|12=draft}}, a kokugakuist ({{ill|Kokugakuist|ja|国学者|12=draft|12=draft}}) (born {{ill|1785|ja|1785|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1869|ja|1869|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ōmura Masujirō|ja|大村益次郎|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military scholar (born {{ill|1824|ja|1824|12=draft|12=draft}}).
