{{Not to be confused with|September 16|qq=September 16}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=九月十六|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 9월 16일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar September|qq=}} '''September 16''' is the 16th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/September (Lunisolar)|qq=}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Emperor Sujin|Emperor Sujin]] 12nd year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|86 BC|ja|紀元前86|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/86 BC|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} [[:en:October 12|October 12]]） – The imperial court conducted its first nationwide population and household registration. * [[:en:Shōryaku|Shōryaku]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|991|ja|991|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/991|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 900}} [[:en:October 26|October 26]]) – [[:en:Emperor Ichijō|Emperor Ichijō]] conferred the title of {{ill|Nyoin-gō|ja|女院号|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nyoin-gō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 女院}} upon the empress dowager, {{ill|Saneko Fujiwara|ja|藤原詮子|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saneko Fujiwara|qq=}}, marking the first instance of a 【female院号】. * [[:en:Ōtoku|Ōtoku]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1086|1086]] [[:en:October 26|October 26]]) – {{ill|Fujiwara Michitoshi|ja|藤原通俊|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara Michitoshi|qq=}} compiled the anthology [[:en:Goshūi Wakashū|Goshūi Wakashū]].
== Births == * {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/An'ei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 安永 (元号)}} 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1779|1779]] [[:en:October 25|October 25]]) – {{ill|Ichikawa Beian|ja|市河米庵|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichikawa Beian|qq=}}, a calligrapher ({{ill|Calligrapher|ja|書家|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Calligrapher|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}) (died {{ill|1858|ja|1858|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1858|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}). * [[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1793|1793]] [[:en:October 20|October 20]]) – [[:en:Watanabe Kazan|Watanabe Kasan]], a rangaku scholar and painter (died {{ill|1841|ja|1841|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1841|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunka]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1804|ja|1804|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1804|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1000}} [[:en:October 19|October 19]]) – {{ill|Hosokawa Saigo|ja|細川斉護|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hosokawa Saigo|qq=}}, the head of the [[:en:Kumamoto Domain|Kumamoto Domain]] (died {{ill|1860|ja|1860|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1860|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1855|ja|1855|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1855|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} [[:en:October 26|October 26]]) – [[:en:Komura Jutarō|Komura Jutaro]], Minister of Foreign Affairs (died {{ill|1911|ja|1911|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1911|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1911 (曖昧さ回避)}}).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Ten'ei|Tennen]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1111|1111]] [[:en:December 7|December 7]]) – [[:en:Ōe no Masafusa|Ōe Masafusa]], a kugyō, Confucian scholar, and poet (born [[:en:1041|1041]]). * [[:en:Genkyū|Genkyū]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1204|1204]] [[:en:November 27|November 27]]) – {{ill|Hojo Masanori|ja|北条政範|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hojo Masanori|qq=}}, a military commander (武将) (born [[:en:1189|1189]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1839|ja|1839|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1839|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} [[:en:December 10|December 10]]) – {{ill|Matsudaira Saiatsu|ja|松平斉厚|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Saiatsu|qq=}}, a daimyō (born [[:en:1783|1783]]). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1856|ja|1856|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1856|qq=}} [[:en:December 2|December 2]]) – {{ill|Ashidai Hirokun|ja|足代弘訓|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashidai Hirokun|qq=}}, a kokugakuist ({{ill|Kokugakuist|1=Kokugakusha|2=ja|3=国学者|ja|国学者|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kokugakuist|13=User:Immanuelle/Kokugakusha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 国学}}) (born [[:en:1785|1785]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1869|ja|1869|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1869|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1000}} [[:en:December 7|December 7]]) – [[:en:Ōmura Masujirō|Ōmura Masujirō]], a military scholar (born {{ill|1824|ja|1824|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1824|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1000}}).
